SIMPLE: ambulator
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ambulator
<hw>Am"bu*la`tor</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who walks about; a walker.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A beetle of the
genus <gen>Lamia</gen>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A genus of birds, or one
of this genus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>An instrument for measuring distances; -- called
also <altname>perambulator</altname>.</def>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ambulatorial</ent>⟦br⟧
